leads.lead_text: Corolla present; panicles terminal, appearing with leaves; leaflets ± petiolulate
Corolla absent; panicles or racemes axillary, appearing before leaves; leaflets sessile
Winter buds dull black; leaflets with 20–40 teeth on each side, clearly outnumbering the number of lateral veins; flowers in panicles
Winter buds brown; leaflets with 8–20 teeth on each side, 1–1.5 times the number of lateral veins; flowers in racemes
